text.tspan: Pull and optionally verify CI images - possibly in parallel for all Python versions.
Tag added to the default naming conventions of Airflow CI/PROD images.
Python major/minor version used in Airflow image for images.
The token used to authenticate to GitHub.
Tags the image as latest and update checksum of all files after pulling. Used in CI to pull
the image built in another job.
Run the operation in parallel on all or selected subset of Python versions.
Maximum number of processes to use while running the operation in parallel.
Space separated list of python versions used for build with multiple versions.
Print verbose information about performed steps.
If dry-run is set, commands are only printed, not executed.
GitHub repository used to pull, push run images.
